abstract: Jailed WikiLeaks founder Julian Assange appeared in a Madrid court via videolink from Britain on Friday as part of an investigation into his allegations that a Spanish firm spied on him while he lived inside the Ecuadorian embassy in London.
snippet: Jailed WikiLeaks founder Julian Assange appeared in a Madrid court via videolink from Britain on Friday as part of an investigation into his allegations that a Spanish firm spied on him while he lived inside the Ecuadorian embassy in London.
lead_paragraph: MADRID — Jailed WikiLeaks founder Julian Assange appeared in a Madrid court via videolink from Britain on Friday as part of an investigation into his allegations that a Spanish firm spied on him while he lived inside the Ecuadorian embassy in London.
headline_main: Wikileaks' Assange Appears in Court in Spain Spying Investigation
headline_print_headline: Wikileaks' Assange Appears in Court in Spain Spying Investigation

abstract: At an exhibition of Sandy Schreier’s fashion collection at the Costume Institute, it’s the pieces by little-known designers that linger in the imagination.
snippet: At an exhibition of Sandy Schreier’s fashion collection at the Costume Institute, it’s the pieces by little-known designers that linger in the imagination.
lead_paragraph: When fashion enters the hallowed halls of an art institution, as a rule, it begins to fall victim to museumitis: the need to justify its presence in the temple of high culture by focusing almost entirely on its craft or conception. This is understandable, but the result can often seem a bit arid; clothes, after all, were made for people, and it is people that animate them. To separate the life of a garment from actual life can also sap it of emotion, and meaning.

abstract: In the landline world there was down time. You left home, you looked around, you saw people, you daydreamed.
snippet: In the landline world there was down time. You left home, you looked around, you saw people, you daydreamed.
lead_paragraph: This is a lament for the landline, a rhapsody for its dial tone, a hymn to the way it connected people. It’s the little things we miss. The landline was a focal point of the home, an antidote to atomization and loneliness, those scourges of our age.

abstract: Testimony ended on Friday in a lawsuit by a group of states led by New York and California seeking to block the merger of Sprint Corp and T-Mobile US Inc, moving the trial a step closer to having a U.S. judge rule on whether the deal violates federal antitrust laws.
snippet: Testimony ended on Friday in a lawsuit by a group of states led by New York and California seeking to block the merger of Sprint Corp and T-Mobile US Inc, moving the trial a step closer to having a U.S. judge rule on whether the deal violates fede...
lead_paragraph: NEW YORK — Testimony ended on Friday in a lawsuit by a group of states led by New York and California seeking to block the merger of Sprint Corp and T-Mobile US Inc, moving the trial a step closer to having a U.S. judge rule on whether the deal violates federal antitrust laws.

headline_print_headline: Testimony Ends in T-Mobile-Sprint Merger Trial in New York

abstract: Swiss bank Coutts & Co Ltd will pay an additional $27.9 million under an addendum to a 2015 non-prosecution agreement, the U.S. Justice Department said on Friday.
snippet: Swiss bank Coutts & Co Ltd will pay an additional $27.9 million under an addendum to a 2015 non-prosecution agreement, the U.S. Justice Department said on Friday.
lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — Swiss bank Coutts & Co Ltd will pay an additional $27.9 million under an addendum to a 2015 non-prosecution agreement, the U.S. Justice Department said on Friday.
headline_main: Coutts & Co to Pay Additional $27.9 Million Under U.S. Agreement
headline_print_headline: Coutts & Co to Pay Additional $27.9 Million Under U.S. Agreement

abstract: A Yale University police officer has been suspended for 30 days and will be reassigned to administrative duty for his involvement in an April shooting that injured an unarmed woman, the school said Friday.
snippet: A Yale University police officer has been suspended for 30 days and will be reassigned to administrative duty for his involvement in an April shooting that injured an unarmed woman, the school said Friday.
lead_paragraph: HARTFORD, Conn. — A Yale University police officer has been suspended for 30 days and will be reassigned to administrative duty for his involvement in an April shooting that injured an unarmed woman, the school said Friday.
headline_main: Yale Suspends Police Officer Involved in April Shooting
headline_print_headline: Yale Suspends Police Officer Involved in April Shooting

abstract: The Illinois Republican Party is ramping up efforts to make voters aware that an anti-Semitic activist and Holocaust denier who won the GOP nomination two years ago is again a candidate for the U.S. Congress, officials said.

headline_main: Illinois GOP Aims to End Holocaust Denier's Run for Congress

abstract: The U.S. National Highway Traffic Safety Administration is holding talks with General Motors Co on the automaker's petition to deploy a limited number of self-driving vehicles on American roads without steering wheels or other human controls, the head of the agency said on Friday.
snippet: The U.S. National Highway Traffic Safety Administration is holding talks with General Motors Co on the automaker's petition to deploy a limited number of self-driving vehicles on American roads without steering wheels or other human controls, the ...
lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — The U.S. National Highway Traffic Safety Administration is holding talks with General Motors Co on the automaker's petition to deploy a limited number of self-driving vehicles on American roads without steering wheels or other human controls, the head of the agency said on Friday.
headline_main: Exclusive: U.S. Talks With GM Over Deploying Self-Driving Cars Without Steering Wheels
